{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.19",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 19 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:2",
      "text": "“ How long will you torment me, and crush me with words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:3",
      "text": "You have reproached me ten times. You aren’t ashamed that you attack me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:4",
      "text": "If it is true that I have erred, my error remains with myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:5",
      "text": "If indeed you will magnify yourselves against me, and plead against me my reproach,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:6",
      "text": "know now that God has subverted me, and has surrounded me with his net.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:7",
      "text": "“ Behold, I cry out of wrong, but I am not heard. I cry for help, but there is no justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:8",
      "text": "He has walled up my way so that I can ’t pass, and has set darkness in my paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:9",
      "text": "He has stripped me of my glory, and taken the crown from my head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:10",
      "text": "He has broken me down on every side, and I am gone. He has plucked my hope up like a tree.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:11",
      "text": "He has also kindled his wrath against me. He counts me among his adversaries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:12",
      "text": "His troops come on together, build a siege ramp against me, and encamp around my tent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:13",
      "text": "“ He has put my brothers far from me. My acquaintances are wholly estranged from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:14",
      "text": "My relatives have gone away. My familiar friends have forgotten me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:15",
      "text": "Those who dwell in my house and my maids consider me a stranger. I am an alien in their sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:16",
      "text": "I call to my servant, and he gives me no answer. I beg him with my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:17",
      "text": "My breath is offensive to my wife. I am loathsome to the children of my own mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:18",
      "text": "Even young children despise me. If I arise, they speak against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:19",
      "text": "All my familiar friends abhor me. They whom I loved have turned against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:20",
      "text": "My bones stick to my skin and to my flesh. I have escaped by the skin of my teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:21",
      "text": "“ Have pity on me. Have pity on me, you my friends, for the hand of God has touched me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:22",
      "text": "Why do you persecute me as God, and are not satisfied with my flesh?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:23",
      "text": "“ Oh that my words were now written! Oh that they were inscribed in a book!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:24",
      "text": "That with an iron pen and lead they were engraved in the rock forever!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:25",
      "text": "But as for me, I know that my Redeemer lives. In the end, he will stand upon the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:26",
      "text": "After my skin is destroyed, then I will see God in my flesh,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:27",
      "text": "whom I, even I, will see on my side. My eyes will see, and not as a stranger. “ My heart is consumed within me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:28",
      "text": "If you say, ‘ How we will persecute him!’ because the root of the matter is found in me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.19.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:29",
      "text": "be afraid of the sword, for wrath brings the punishments of the sword, that you may know there is a judgment.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
